To align a row of divs to the right using flexbox, you can use the `flex-direction` property to set it to `row-reverse`, and then use the `align-items` property to set it to `flex-end`. Here's an example:
```css
.row {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: row-reverse;
  align-items: flex-end;
}
```
And here's how you can use this CSS in your HTML:
```html
<div class="row">
  <div>Div 1</div>
  <div>Div 2</div>
  <div>Div 3</div>
</div>
```
In this example, the three divs will be aligned to the right in a row.
Note that you can also use the `justify-content` property instead of `align-items` to achieve the same result, by setting it to `flex-end`. Here's an example:
```css
.row {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: row-reverse;
  justify-content: flex-end;
}
```<|im_sep|>
